<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="fit-n">fit <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /fɪt/    美 /fɪt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1c-u">1.<strong>[C] &amp; [U] [常与形容词连用] 适合；合身 (的衣服)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Your jacket is a <strong>nice fit</strong>.
你的夹克衫很合身。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My new shoes are a <strong>tight fit</strong>. 
我的新鞋挤脚。</p></div>

<h4 id="2c">2.<strong>[C] (病的) 发作； (感情等的) 突发：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He had a violent <strong>coughing fits</strong>. 
他一阵剧烈咳嗽。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She quit her job in <strong>a fit of</strong> temper
她一怒之下辞掉了工作。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>fitness /'fɪtnəs/ n [U]   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>a fitness centre</strong>
健身中心</p></div></div>